   <b>OBJECTIVE</b>

   </br>A Project Manager plans and leads projects for Nevoĺs clients
   through their entire life cycle from requirements gathering
   to production implementation and subsequent support. Nevo
   expects Project Managers to succeed in the duties and
   responsibilities defined for the role.</br>

   <b>MAJOR DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText">

   </li><li>Define and drive agreement on project vision, requirements, and scope and manage their change over the project life

   </li><li>Define specific project deliverables and acceptance criteria, ensure the professional and technical quality of Nevoĺs deliverables, and contribute to deliverables where required

   </li><li>Develop project schedules, estimates, budgets, and milestones

   </li><li>Plan, direct and control project resources, activities, and costs, ensuring success against features, schedule, budget, quality objectives, and clientĺs project goals

   </li><li>Define quality goals and establish and manage a strategy to achieve quality in technical solutions, process, and deliverables

   </li><li>Select and manage the tools and resources appropriate for project success

   </li><li>Direct project teams, ensuring the right resources are assigned and work productively

   </li><li>Develop risk management plan and manage risks over the course of the project

   </li><li>Develop project communications plan and communicate effectively with all stakeholders

   </li><li>Lead and contribute to Nevo proposal and business development efforts

   </li><li>Generate positive business results for Nevo
   </li></ul>

   <b>ESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText">

   </li><li>Has BS or BA in a technical field or equivalent technical experience and 5+ years of professional work experience, including 2+ years in professional services or consulting

   </li><li>Has 2+ years project management experience managing 2 or more multidisciplinary project teams of at least 5 people

   </li><li>Demonstrated successes managing software development teams

   </li><li>Demonstrated successes managing customer relationships

   </li><li>Proven problem solving and people management skills

   </li><li>Demonstrates strong understanding of software development methodologies, especially agile software development approaches

   </li><li>Exhibits excellent communication and interpersonal skills with an appreciation for and ability to communicate with and respond to the needs of diverse audiences

   </li><li>Demonstrates excellent writing skills; the ability to write clear, concise, comprehensive documents

   </li><li>Experienced with projects for clients in the Financial Services sector

   </li><li>Experienced managing projects in a consulting / professional services environment
   </li></ul>

   <b>DESIRABLE QUALIFICATIONS</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText">

   </li><li>Experienced with UML-based design methodology, Use Case Analysis, prototyping, iterative development, integrated quality assurance, etc.

   </li><li>Comfortable speaking to groups in both formal and informal situations

   </li><li>Able to facilitate client work sessions and to lead the requirements gathering process

   </li><li>Experienced with improving, creating, and documenting effective business processes

   </li><li>Comfortable in a multi-task, deadline-oriented environment

   </li><li>Experienced with the technology of web based solutions utilizing J2EE and IBM WebSphere and/or .Net
   </li></ul>


